1. Create a GitHub Account
           Visit GitHub: Go to GitHub.com.
            Sign Up:
            Click on the "Sign up" button.
            Fill in your details (username, email, and password).
             Verify your email and complete the setup process.
2. Create a Repository
             Log in to GitHub: Use your newly created account credentials.
             Go to the "Repositories" tab: Click on your profile picture (top-right corner) and select "Your repositories."
Click "New":
Add a repository name (e.g., MyFirstRepo).
           Optionally, add a description.
           Choose whether the repository will be public or private.
             Check the box "Add a README file" (recommended).
           Click "Create repository."
3. Save a File to the Repository
          Option 1: Upload via GitHub Website
          Open the repository: Go to your newly created repository.
            Upload a file:
           Click the "Add file" button, then choose "Upload files."
        Drag and drop files or click to select files from your computer.
        Add a commit message (e.g., "Added initial file").
        Click "Commit changes" to save.

  
